Description: Small clay bobbin made of a fine brown Nile clay that was consolidated after excavation leading to a darker colouration. The shape is that of a bobbin with a cylindrical part with 0.7 cm lengths in the middle and two rounded ends with a slightly larger diameter. One end is partly eroded. Used as bobbin or ear-plug?
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Amara West (Nubia), D15, square S, level 1 (sand)
Bibliographic references: Spencer 1997 / Amara West I, The Architectural Report (p. 210)
